positions.comment: Still in - and enjoying thoroughly, La Coruna, NW corner of Spain
Mostly around the corner; Cape Finisterre is next; now in Ria Camarinas
Soft winds invited us around Cabo Finisterre; anchored Ensenada de San Francisco
Moved to Muros for the weekend sea festival; sunny and warm when not foggy
Back to Portosin for ''work day'' of laundry, boat scrub and such
Moved to Ria de Arousa; lovely anchorage off sandy playa, beautiful weather
Anchored off VillaGarcia, where we''ll board Adrian and Julia EARLY Tues.
Anchored in Ria de Vigo after visiting trashy Isla de Cies and its plastic baggies
Berthed Club Nautico Vigo with a slime line holding us off the pontoon
Shifted to Bayona at mouth of Vigo Ria; many cruisers, all going somewhere
Departed Spain for Viana do Costello, Portugal; now to find the officials!
Berthed in Figueira da Foz; yet more officials and paperwork but it's nice
Further south to Piniche; minimal berthing and no anchoring...back to rafting!
Another murky, hazy motorsail, arriving Lisbon's outskirts - Cascais anchorage
Moved up the Tejo R. to Lisbon; will haul on Monday, Oct. 5th
Stripping WHOOSH in prep for storage ashore, but also enjoying seeing Lisbon
Hot days, cool evenings, lots to see and lots to do on the boat; Lisbon is great
Moved to Tagus Yacht Center, the shipyard where we'll leave WHOOSH; haul Wed
WHOOSH in steel cradle ashore, stripped and looking forlorn; fly back Wed.
